.TH EYECALIB 1 "2026" "tobii4c" "User Commands"

.SH NAME
eyecalib \- Tobii Eye Tracker X11 gaze calibration tool

.SH SYNOPSIS
.B eyecalib
.RI [ options ]

.SH DESCRIPTION
.B eyecalib
provides fullscreen calibration for the Tobii Eye Tracker 4C
under Linux/X11.

The utility collects gaze samples for a 3x3 calibration mesh
used by:

.B eyemouse

Calibration improves:

- Fullscreen reachability
- Edge precision
- Cursor stability
- Corner access
- Asymmetric distortion correction

.SH OPTIONS

.TP
.B -h, --help
Show command line help.

.TP
.B --debug
Enable verbose debug output on stderr.
Covers Tobii DB import, device init, X11 setup, per-point calibration
results, sample counts, and config save.
Output lines are prefixed with
.BR [DBG] .

.TP
.B --debuggaze
Enable verbose gaze output on stderr.
Covers every gaze sample received during calibration, validity checks,
out-of-range detection, and sensor offset application.
Output lines are prefixed with
.BR [GAZE] .
This flag is high frequency and should be redirected to a file
when used together with
.BR --debug .

.SH CALIBRATION PROCESS
The calibration process:

.nf
fullscreen targets
    -> gaze sample collection
    -> sample filtering
    -> calibration mesh generation
    -> persistent calibration storage
.fi

.SH CALIBRATION TARGETS
The calibration uses a 3x3 fullscreen target layout:

.nf
P00  P01  P02
P10  P11  P12
P20  P21  P22
.fi

Targets are intentionally placed near display borders
to improve fullscreen reachability.

.SH CALIBRATION STORAGE
Calibration data is written to:

.nf
~/.local/tobii_4c/calx11.conf
.fi

Example:

.nf
0.052524 0.075656 0.050000 0.050000
.fi

Format:

.nf
raw_x raw_y target_x target_y
.fi

.SH CALIBRATION MATHEMATICS
Each calibration sample stores:

- Measured Tobii gaze position
- Expected screen position

Example:

.nf
0.523789 0.455566 -> 0.500000 0.500000
.fi

Meaning:

- Tracker measured 52.4% horizontal gaze
- Actual target was 50%

The runtime later derives local barycentric mesh warp correction.

.SH BARYCENTRIC MESH MAPPING
The warp correction is derived from calibration samples.

The 3x3 mesh is split into 8 triangles.
For every gaze sample the runtime:

.IP 1. 4
Selects the containing triangle
.IP 2. 4
Calculates barycentric coordinates
.IP 3. 4
Interpolates local warped screen coordinates

This improves:

- Fullscreen reachability
- Fullscreen coverage
- Corner precision

.fi

.SH RUNTIME FILTERING
Calibration performs:

- Invalid sample rejection
- Realtime smoothing
- Sample stabilization
- Gaze averaging

This reduces:

- Jitter
- Unstable fixation
- Noisy gaze samples

.SH X11 REQUIREMENT
The calibration utility currently requires:

- X11
- Fullscreen override-redirect windows
- X11 pointer control

Wayland is unsupported.

Check:

.nf
$ echo $XDG_SESSION_TYPE
x11
.fi

.SH FILES
.nf
~/.local/tobii_4c/calx11.conf
.fi

.SH CURRENT STABLE RUNTIME
The current stable runtime actively uses:

- Barycentric interpolation
- 3x3 calibration mesh
- X11 cursor mapping
- Realtime smoothing

The following features are experimental or incomplete:

- Bootstrap geometry import
- C12 runtime
- Projective warp
- Head compensated reprojection
- Full 3D geometry correction

.SH EXAMPLE
Run calibration:

.nf
$ eyecalib
.fi

Run with debug output:

.nf
$ eyecalib --debug
.fi

Run with gaze debug (high frequency):

.nf
$ eyecalib --debuggaze
.fi

All debug output to log file:

.nf
$ eyecalib --debug --debuggaze 2>eyecalib.log
.fi

Run eyemouse afterwards:

.nf
$ eyemouse
.fi

.SH SEE ALSO
.BR eyemouse (1)

